Subject: Re: [T2] 1700 upgrade to 2000, difficulties

on 8/16/04 10:23, Michael Knight related:

> Is the bottom end, ie short block of a 1700 suitable or interchangable with
> P/C and heads for a 2.0L?

No.

> If I strip down the engine to a short block and replace the P/C and Heads
> from the 1700 with the 2.0L  P/C and Heads, would this be a direct bolt on
> application?

No again. the piston pin height is different, so you cannot use 1.7/1.8
crank and rods with 2l pistons.

> Would the rods, crank and cam be suitable for use without modification?

cam is interchangeable, sort of.

> Is there a difference in stroke fom the 1700 to the 2000?

1700 is 66mm stroke. 2000 is 71mm.


